BRIEFING:
MODERATE TRADES EXPECTED THROUGH TOMORROW AS A COLD FRONT APPROACHES FROM THE NORTHWEST. WINDS WILL FOCUS LOW CLOUDS AND SHOWERS OVER WINDWARD AND MAUKA AREAS, WITH OCCASIONAL SPILLOVER TO LEEWARD AREAS. BRIEF MVFR CONDITIONS CAN BE EXPECTED IN SHOWERS. OTHERWISE, VFR SHOULD PREVAIL.
NO AIRMETS ARE IN EFFECT AND NONE ARE ANTICIPATED TO BE NEEDED OVER THE NEXT 24 HOURS.
THREAT: NO SIGMETS IN AREA OF OPERATION.
